sourcesContent:
import React from 'react'; import "./Resume.css"; function Resume() { return (
Sugene Mulpuri
Software Developer and Email Marketing Professional

Languages and Technologies

Languages:
  • HTML5
  • CSS3
  • PHP
  • JavaScript
  • SQL
  • AMPScript
  • RPL
  • React
  • Angular
  • TypeScript
  • Node.js
  • Express
  • Heroku
  • Python
  • Selenium
Technologies:
  • Salesforce Marketing Cloud
  • Pardot
  • Oracle Responsys
  • Emarsys
  • Visual Studio
  • Litmus
  • Email On Acid
  • WordPress
  • Canva
  • Adobe Photoshop
  • Adobe InDesign
  • Microsoft Office Suite

Experience

Aligned HQ | Training Model Expert | October 2025-present
  • Testing conversational AI training models released by Meta for ratability and adherence to guidelines.
Computers To Go | Front-End Developer Internship | March 2025-August 2025
  • Played a key role in developing and maintaining a custom patient management web application using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and PHP, contributing to a 10% increase in clinician productivity and patient engagement.
  • Built and customized websites using WordPress and Colibri plugin, incorporating HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and PHP for dynamic, responsive layouts.
  • Edited visual content using Canva, enhancing UI consistency and overall site appeal across multiple projects.
  • Implemented on-page SEO strategies to provide actionable data for the Digital Marketing team.
  • Collaborated closely with senior developers and marketers to ensure performance optimization, user experience, and branding alignment.
Self-Directed Software Development and QA Apprenticeship | February 2024-March 2025
  • Explored software development fundamentals through bootcamp content, tutorials, and self-paced projects, focusing on core programming concepts and modern development practices.
  • Shadowed a QA engineer at a small SaaS company through an informal mentorship, gaining exposure to day-to-day testing workflows including sprint planning, bug tracking, and test execution.
  • Leveraged AI tools such as GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT to enhance code writing, accelerate debugging, and support documentation tasks.
  • Studied generative AI and prompt engineering to apply best practices to technical solutions and overall productivity.
Kelsey-Seybold Clinic | Email Marketing Specialist | March 2022-January 2024
  • Developed 1,000+ client-facing emails using HTML, CSS, AMPScript, and Salesforce Marketing Cloud Content Builder tools, contributing to a yearly email production rate increase of 110% from 2022 to 2023.
  • Implemented a continuous improvement result-based strategy to schedule and deploy approved email messages in SFMC email studio that led to a 10% increase in open rate across all business channel emails from 2022 to 2023.
  • Constructed 20+ custom component based email templates to improve the systematic organization of email content materials, from this method our team increased the average email production speed by 80%.
  • Assembled 20+ custom data extensions from Epic patient data contributing to the company’s ability to send messages to new subscribers.
  • Utilized Adobe Photoshop and Adobe Illustrator to create 100+ branded reusable content graphics to improve the email design process speed by 30%.
  • Collaborated with project administrators to create a workflow process that meets the time and efficiency requirements of the business.
Covetrus | Email Developer | September 2021-January 2022
  • Developed 100+ client-facing emails using MJML, HTML, CSS, and AMPScript in Salesforce Pardot.
  • Utilized scripting languages to synchronize MJML templates with a back-end relational database.
  • Utilized Litmus to troubleshoot and test email previews across Inbox providers including Gmail, Yahoo and Microsoft Outlook.
  • Collaborated with marketing engineers to filter audience lists, automate email life cycles, and deploy marketing campaigns in Salesforce Pardot and Emarsys Systems.
  • Enabled dark mode on 10+ targeted campaigns.
Quicken Loans | Email Programmer | April 2020-June 2021
  • Built 500+ dynamic client-facing emails using HTML, CSS, and AMPScript in Salesforce Marketing Cloud.
  • Established data-implementing code fragments to communicate across all SFMC business units improving the efficiency of the workflow process by 80%.
  • Used SFMC Content Builder to rebuild 100+ marketing emails in rebranding initiatives for 3+ business areas.
  • Established sender profiles in SFMC Email Studio to improve efficiency of proof retrieval for email finalization processes.
  • Used Microsoft Excel to organize campaigns by respective attributes for facilitation of A/B testing.
  • Used SQL to retrieve data points for use in personalization of campaigns.
  • Developed a mobile responsive signature HTML content block for a high profile weekly newsletter campaign that improved accessibility by 30%.
  • Utilized system database to track generated leads.
  • Enabled UTM tracking on 10+ marketing campaigns improving efficiency of metric analysis process by 40%.
  • Collaborated with requesters, strategists, and designers to create a product that meets the goals of the business.
Modis | Document Developer | November 2019-April 2020
  • Utilized JavaScript to dynamically design title and escrow documents in Adobe Experience Manager, our team reduced the Final Policy Queue by over 14700 orders.
  • Built 100+ SQL scripts to insert and organize documents in the Amrock database.
  • Pushed and tested documents across multiple development environments to prepare for their use in business production.
  • Closely collaborated with Product Owners and Business Leaders to tailor documents to specific needs of the business.
Medical Arts Building | Billing Associate | December 2017-November 2019
  • Facilitated digital transmission of patient demographic and EKG data using Epic HyperSpace, increasing the rate of billing flow by 80%.
Ascension Information Services | Information Technology Intern | June 2017-December 2017
  • Installed and configured 30+ updated workstations across Mid-Michigan region, improving Radiologist workflow by over 70%.
  • Programmed 10+ bash scripts on Radiologist workstations to provide automated monthly alerts and self-maintenance.

Projects

Don't Do It | Interactive Entertainment Website | Grand Circus Training Project | August 2019-September 2019
  • Developed 4+ variations of “Buzzfeed” type quizzes and multiple advice columns by implementing a back-end with relational databases using Express, Node.js and various SQL databases.
  • Created 5+ components to improve UI and logic using Angular and JavaScript, increasing render performance by over 30%.
  • Implemented a GIPHY API Key and inserted the API in a timer algorithm, increasing GIF occurrences on respective pages by 5+ per minute.
Pokématch | Memory Matching Game | Grand Circus Training Project | July 2019-August 2019
  • Designed a custom algorithm in JavaScript to implement 30+ unique cards for each player from a 200+ item database, increasing character variance by 300%.
  • Implemented responsiveness and playability for 10+ devices including mobile and tablet by using CSS3 with flexbox and grid system.
  • Developed timer component using 5+ custom algorithms, allowing player scores to be calculated and recorded to score database, increasing user engagement by 80%.

Education

M.S. Software Development | Boston University | January 2027
Applied Generative AI Specialization | Simplilearn | December 2025
Career Essentials in Generative AI | Microsoft | January 2025
Think Outside the Inbox: Email Marketing | Coursera | December 2023
Foundations of Digital Marketing and E-commerce | Coursera | November 2023
Salesforce Marketing Cloud Consultant | Udemy | February 2023
Salesforce Marketing Cloud Email Specialist | Udemy | July 2022
Front-End Development | Grand Circus | September 2019
Bachelors of Science: Psychology | Michigan State University | August 2016
Certified Medical Transcriptionist | Saginaw Valley State University | April 2016
